[size=4][b]What[/b][/size]

[size=3]Speed up every crafting-related activity in the game. Each speedup is an independent toggle so you can keep some vanilla and accelerate others.[/size]

[size=3][b]Main multiplier[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Craft Speed Multiplier[/b] — applies to player-driven crafts at regular workbenches (anvils, alchemy workbenches, cooking, study desks, etc.). Default 2×. Adjustable slider. Repair crafts (soul machines, broken buildings) are intentionally excluded — applying the multiplier to them could make the per-frame energy cost exceed your max energy and soft-lock the repair.[/size]
[*][size=3]Gardens, composting, and zombie-worked stations are not covered by this multiplier — each has its own dedicated toggle further down, so you can leave the main multiplier low and only crank up the stations you care about.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Build and destroy[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Faster Build And Destroy[/b] — speeds up the progress bar on the build/destroy action so placing and removing structures is quicker.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Production stations[/b][/size]
[size=3]Each of these has its own on/off toggle plus an independent speed slider, so you can crank one up and leave the rest alone.[/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Composting[/b] — the compost bin cycles faster.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Your Garden[/b] — the player's own garden beds grow quicker.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Refugee Garden[/b] — refugee-camp garden beds grow quicker.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Zombie Garden[/b] — zombie-worked garden beds grow quicker.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Zombie Mines[/b] — zombie-worked ore-mining crafters in the stone yard, marble deposit, and iron mine produce faster. (The sawmill in the zombie mill zone is covered by its own toggle below.)[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Zombie Sawmill[/b] — zombie-worked sawmill produces faster.[/size]
[*][size=3][b]Zombie Vineyard[/b] — zombie-worked vineyard produces faster.[/size]
[/list]

[size=3][b]Other[/b][/size]
[list]
[*][size=3][b]Main menu update notice[/b] — flags when a newer version of this mod (or other mods in my collection) is available on Nexus. Click an entry to open its Nexus page. Opt-out via "Check for Updates".[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Other mods of mine you might like[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/42]Exhaust-less[/url] — half-cost / unlimited-stat options. Combine with FasterCraft for faster crafts at lower energy cost.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/57]Queue Everything[/url] — queue whole batches of crafts. QE reads FasterCraft's multipliers, so the live totals you see already reflect the faster times.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/62]Where's Ma' Storage[/url] — one shared inventory across workstations, so every sped-up bench has access to your pooled materials.[/size]
[*][size=3][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/70]Give Me Moar[/url] — multipliers for drops and craft outputs. Pairs nicely with higher production speeds.[/size]
[/list]

[size=4][b]Configuration[/b][/size]

[size=3]If you installed the required [url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack[/url] and this mod is configurable, press F1 in-game to open the config interface.[/size]

[size=4][b]Requirements[/b][/size]

[list]
[*][url=https://www.nexusmods.com/graveyardkeeper/mods/79][size=3]Graveyard Keeper BepInEx 5 Pack at Graveyard Keeper Nexus - Mods and community (nexusmods.com)[/size][/url]
[/list]
[size=4][b]Installation[/b][/size]

[size=3]Installation using Vortex is the recommended installation method. If you wish to install manually, extract the contents of the mod archive into:

[code]...&#92;steamapps&#92;common&#92;Graveyard Keeper&#92;BepInEx[/code][/size]

